      <Text>
        <Sent id="2.1">I'd use Netscape 3.x and 4.x, a version of MS Internet Explorer (as you can't have two versions on the same machine to my knowledge), a text browser such as lynx., PwWebSpeak for the voice browser and maybe Opera if you have extra time and money. </Sent>
        <Sent id="2.2">Also to be considered is the use of a general screen reader such as Jaws For Windows. </Sent>
        <Sent id="2.3">Use of tools such as bobby and HTML validators is also essential. </Sent>
        <Sent id="2.4">It might be sensible to have disabled users actually do the testing. 
</Sent>
        <Sent id="2.5">See also: 
</Sent>
        <Sent id="2.6">http://www.eeicom.com/dcwebmasters/pwd/ 
</Sent>
        <Sent id="2.7">http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/Grid/5447/access.html (not yet 
</Sent>
        <Sent id="2.8">refined) 
</Sent>
        <Sent id="2.9">-Jamie Fox 
</Sent>
